The paper proposes a method for learning highly compressible neural network weights, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also applies the proposed method to train neural networks for image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship between the proposed compressibility loss and sparsity, which is a topic related to neural networks and optimization, and thus could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the entropy of the non-zero parts of the signal, which is a topic related to information theory, and thus could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
